OL,3,CThe whisky distillery helping put town
OL,4,Con the tourist map
OL,6,FChris Conway went to Wooler to see how
OL,7,Fwhisky is having an impact on the
OL,8,Ftown's economic outlook for .
OL,10,FThe re-ignition of a tradition not
OL,11,Fseen in Northumberland for more than
OL,12,F200 years is helping to bring more
OL,13,Fpeople to one of the county's lesser
OL,14,Fknown tourist towns.
OL,16,FWooler, the gateway to the Cheviot
OL,17,FHills, is home to Ad Gefrin - an
OL,18,Fancient site once home to Northumbrian
OL,19,Froyalty.
